        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 4:33AM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 433 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Roxton, or 11 miles southwest of Paris, moving north at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Sumner, Paris, and Lake Gibbons around 440 AM CDT.
Lake Crook around 445 AM CDT.
Camp Maxey and Pat Mayse Lake around 450 AM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Toco, East Direct,
Atlas, Noble, Forest Chapel, Broadway Junction, Midcity, Garretts
Bluff, Direct, and Howland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for
north central Texas.</instruction>
